Legs (Figs 1, 6-9). Generally, morphology typical for species of Lasiobelba ( Bernini 1973 ; Ohkubo 2001 ;
Ermilov and Kaluz 2012
). Dorsal side of each claw in all tarsi with two rows of small teeth (tl). Formulae of leg setation and solenidia: I (1 -5-2-4- 20) [1 -2- 2], II (1 -5-2-4- 16) [1 -1- 2], III (2 -3-1-3- 15) [1 -1- 0], IV (1 -2-2-3- 12) [0 -1- 0]; homology of setae and solenidia indicated in Table 1. Setae p setiform on tarsi I, very short, conical on tarsi II-IV . Famulus (ε) setiform, straight, pointed, inserted posteriorly to solenidion ω 1.
